# CTG encrypted credential vault (Hacker Planet LLC)

Andy prefers the **encrypted open-source credential vault** for all CTG lab username/password pairs going forward.

## Canonical storage

| Store | Use |
|-------|-----|
| **`Ctg-CredentialVault.ps1`** | Username/password entries (Kali SSH, router admin, dashboards) — title **`Kali SSH`** for deploy scripts |
| **`Protect-CtgSecrets.ps1`** | Legacy flat secrets, API tokens, PII phone (`CTG_PII_*`) |

## Security rules (mandatory)

- **Master password + optional DPAPI hybrid** (`-InitVault -WithDpapiWrap`, `-UnlockVault -UseWindowsUser`).
- **Never commit secrets** — vault at `%USERPROFILE%\Backups\.vault\credentials.vault` is gitignored.
- **Never paste real passwords** into chat, rules, docs, or scripts — placeholders only in repo.
- Crypto: Argon2id/scrypt KDF + AES-256-GCM (`core/ctg_vault.py`); constant-time compare patterns.
- Recovery master password in **DuckDuckGo Password Manager** — not in git.

## Script integration

Lab deploy/flash with `-UseSecretVault` resolves credential vault title **`Kali SSH`** first, then DPAPI `KALI_SSH_USER` / `KALI_SSH_PASSWORD`.

See `docs/SECRET_VAULT.md` and `docs/SECURITY_HARDENING.md`.
